        <header class="post-header">
            <h1 class="post-title">What is hack4fem?</h1>
        </header>

        <section class="post-content">
            <p>The Hack for Feminism group (hack4fem for short) focuses on combining engineering with activism.</p>

<p>Our mission is <strong>to engage technically-minded people in hands-on work in support of feminism and feminist causes.</strong> By connecting people through our events, we hope to build a <strong>self-sustaining and supportive network</strong> of technically-minded feminists. We organize a series of events, including the hack4fem convention.</p>

<p>We want to help engineers get involved in feminist issues, connect scientists and mathematicians doing research relevant to feminism, provide resources for programmers working to address feminist issues, and more. We plan on showcasing the funny and creative sides of feminism and having a boatload of fun â€“ come join us!</p>
        </section>

